In her speech, Vice President Harris emphasizes the American spirit of aspiration and resilience. She highlights historical figures such as Abraham Lincoln and Dr. Martin Luther King Jr. who fought for a better future, as well as the women who fought for equal rights and the authors of the Bill of Rights who championed freedoms. She also recognizes the determination and hard work of scientists, parents, innovators, educators, and all those building better lives for themselves and their communities. Vice President Harris calls upon Americans to have the courage to see beyond crisis, to do what is hard and good, and to unite as a nation. She concludes by expressing gratitude and invoking a blessing for America.